Day 6: Exported names

After working with #JavaScript and his modules (first CommonJS and then #ES6 modules) I was curious to know how they worked on #Go. Or well… its counterpart. Because in Go it's more about exported or unexported names.

The overview is as follows: the names that are exported are those that begin with a capital letter, those that start with lowercase are unexported and are not accessible outside of their package.

To stop and think that in today’s day and age, each individual has the potential of reaching millions of people through technology is a pretty thrilling thought. We have the tools and the ability to create anything our mind can conceptualize and the platforms in order to share it with the world. As a society, we hold more power than ever before. We are more capable than ever. That’s a lot of influence. Now think, how are you using it to change the world and to bring good? How are you using it to leave the world in a better place than before? How are you using it to serve people? A friend recently shared with me their vision “to reach 100 million people”  and it’s something that has stuck with me and deeply inspired me. How do you use your influence?
